<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="385" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Loubet</persName> to
                                President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-04"><hi rend="smallcaps">September</hi> 4,
                                    1902</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The report of the awful accident to which you came near falling a victim
                            has just reached me, and I hear that you have happily escaped. I wish to
                            express to you my very sincere felicitations and to renew to you the
                            assurance of my constant friendship.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Emilé Loubet</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>